Somalia’s health ministry has announced that the country is now able to test for coronavirus at the capital, Mogadishu. Previously samples were being flown over 1,200km (742 miles) away to Kenya’s capital, Nairobi, for testing. The ministry’s National Public Health Research Laboratory (NPHRL) has now been equipped to carry out the tests. Here is the ministry’s tweet that showcased the laboratory;  HE. @AbikarDr Informs the public that, from today, the testing for COVID19 will be done at the @MoH_Somalia NPHRL in Mogadishu. 